+# Constraint-Based Event Scheduler — Design
+
+## Architecture
+
+Three source files:
+- `src/types.ts` — All TypeScript interfaces (Event, Room, ScheduleOptions, Assignment, ScheduleResult)
+- `src/scheduler.ts` — Core scheduling logic
+- `src/index.ts` — Re-exports schedule function and types
+
+## Algorithm
+
+### Phase 1: Validation
+- Build prerequisite dependency graph
+- Detect cycles using DFS with coloring (white/gray/black). Throw error on any cycle including self-references.
+
+### Phase 2: Ordering
+- Topological sort of events respecting prerequisites
+- Within same topological level, sort by "most constrained first":
+  - Fewer eligible rooms (rooms with sufficient capacity) = more constrained
+  - Longer duration = more constrained
+  - More prerequisites = more constrained
+
+### Phase 3: Assignment
+- For each event in order:
+  1. Compute earliest possible start time based on prerequisite completion times + gap
+  2. Try preferred room first if specified and has capacity
+  3. For each eligible room, find earliest available slot (respecting room gaps)
+  4. Pick the assignment that starts earliest; break ties by preferred room
+- If no valid placement exists, add to unscheduled list
+
+### Phase 4: Optimization
+- After initial greedy pass, if any events are unscheduled:
+  - Try rescheduling: remove each scheduled event, attempt to place unscheduled events, then re-place removed event
+  - Accept swap if net scheduled count increases
+
+## Constraints Applied
+- Room capacity: event.attendees <= room.capacity
+- Time window: startTime >= options.startTime && endTime <= options.endTime
+- Room gaps: between consecutive events in same room, gap >= options.gap (default 15)
+- Prerequisite gaps: prerequisite endTime + gap <= dependent startTime
+- Preferred room: tried first but not hard constraint
+
+## Defaults
+- event.attendees defaults to 1
+- options.gap defaults to 15
